  grammar:[
    {id:"N5L20g1",point:"〜てあげる / 〜てもらう / 〜てくれる (giving & receiving favors)",explanation:"てあげる = I do favor for someone. てもらう = I receive favor from someone (focus on receiver). てくれる = someone does favor for me (focus on giver). に marks the person.",examples:["友達に本を貸してあげました。 (I lent a book to my friend.)","友達に写真を撮ってもらいました。 (I had my friend take a photo.)","友達が教えてくれました。 (My friend taught me.)"],listening:"あげる = I give favor. もらう = I receive favor. くれる = someone gives favor to me.",production:"Make 3 sentences each with てあげる, てもらう, てくれる."},
    {id:"N5L20g2",point:"Direction of giving/receiving",explanation:"あげる: I → others (outgoing). くれる: others → me (incoming, focus on giver). もらう: I ← others (incoming, focus on receiver). Never use あげる for giving to superiors — use さしあげる.",examples:["私は母に花をあげました。 (I gave flowers to my mother.)","母は私にセーターをくれました。 (My mother gave me a sweater.)","私は母にセーターをもらいました。 (I received a sweater from my mother.)"],listening:"あげる = outgoing. くれる/もらう = incoming. Same event, different perspective.",production:"Describe the same gift event from 3 perspectives using あげる, くれる, もらう."}
  ],
